          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two entirely different experimental arrangements were",
                " used.  The  first,  at  angles  1.2 and 1.5 degrees,",
                " utilised a shadow beam geometry in which the elastic",
                " cross  section was obtained by comparing the area of",
                " the elastic peak to the neighbouring Compton peak in",
                " the same scattered spectrum. The second measurement,",
                " for the range of angles 25 - 140 degrees,  used  the",
                " conventional  method  of  comparing the intensity of",
                " elastically  scattered  g-line  with  that  in   the",
                " incident beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
